27:57.240 --> 27:59.219
(Birdsong)

28:21.200 --> 28:23.065
When shall we go to London?

28:25.360 --> 28:26.941
Go when you please.

28:31.000 --> 28:35.187
You cannot still be angry...
because of the incident with the boy.

28:35.360 --> 28:38.625
- You surely don't suggest...
- That we're incompatible?

28:39.640 --> 28:43.417
That our marriage is foundering
on suspicion and jealousy?

28:44.440 --> 28:47.705
That your objection to the boy
is really your hatred of Ross?

28:49.960 --> 28:53.339
- I wondered when that name would occur.
- Are you not jealous of hIm?

28:54.360 --> 28:58.262
Is suspicion not eating you up?
Poisoning your family life?

28:58.440 --> 29:01.341
Turning your achievements
to bitterness and gall?

29:02.680 --> 29:06.025
There can be no future for our marriage,
if that is the case.

29:13.600 --> 29:15.579
(Door slams)

29:16.600 --> 29:19.160
Make haste, quiet about it.

29:20.720 --> 29:23.905
That's it. Heave. One, two, three, heave!

29:26.960 --> 29:28.746
Make fast.

29:32.400 --> 29:36.097
Secure it at the back.
Quick about it. Quick about it.

29:36.280 --> 29:38.942
Ready? And heave!

30:13.920 --> 30:16.377
Oh, maid, come home.
There's a visitor.

30:16.560 --> 30:18.300
I can't now. Drake needs me.

30:19.360 --> 30:23.387
Begging your pardon.
It is one I b'la you wish to see.

30:26.640 --> 30:29.017
I can stay and make myself useful.

30:30.640 --> 30:32.505
No, it isn't right, Prudie.

30:32.680 --> 30:36.821
How oft do the men take a fancy
to another woman and sometimes act on it?

30:37.000 --> 30:39.104
I would never.
It would break Ross's heart.

30:39.280 --> 30:41.339
No, I must give up all thoughts of him.

30:43.040 --> 30:45.179
As Ross gave up
all thought of Elizabeth for me.

30:45.360 --> 30:46.907
Did he?

30:47.080 --> 30:48.866
Are you sure?

31:13.640 --> 31:16.780
I only tell you of it
for you know it means naught.

31:19.120 --> 31:21.680
- It is but a dalliance.
- A dalliance?

31:22.720 --> 31:24.585
So...

31:24.760 --> 31:29.106
'ee may have one of your own,
without troubling your conscience.

31:34.840 --> 31:36.819
Go home, Prudie.

31:41.640 --> 31:43.779
(Coos)

31:49.000 --> 31:51.343
Well, my dear...

31:51.520 --> 31:54.421
I trust you are feeling rested
and ready to resume your...

31:54.600 --> 31:56.909
No, Ossie.

31:57.840 --> 32:00.024
My dear, I think you forget yourself.

32:00.200 --> 32:03.829
I come in all friendliness,
intending to give the natural...

32:04.000 --> 32:05.217
I said no.

32:08.280 --> 32:10.180
You will leave this room

32:10.360 --> 32:12.624
and never return.

32:15.000 --> 32:17.264
Can I believe my ears?

32:17.440 --> 32:21.422
Are you so wilful, so headstrong, so...

32:21.600 --> 32:24.706
Blind? No.

32:24.880 --> 32:26.859
Nor half-witted neither.

32:30.800 --> 32:34.065
My sister is with child.

32:40.480 --> 32:44.905
Despite your attempts to sedate me,
I have not been deaf all of the time.

32:45.080 --> 32:47.389
You must realise it was not my fault.

32:47.560 --> 32:51.303
That girl has some evil in her
which makes a man possessed.

32:52.000 --> 32:55.743
But now, by the grace of God,
I have returned to you,

32:55.920 --> 33:01.187
so let us pray together and then...
happily resume our marriage.

33:01.360 --> 33:02.907
Neven

33:06.120 --> 33:09.146
You have no right to deny me.

33:12.240 --> 33:16.461
I am your husband
and you will do as I command.

33:16.640 --> 33:18.619
I will kill your son!

33:20.840 --> 33:25.504
So help me, God, if you do so much
as approach me again, I will smother him.

33:25.680 --> 33:28.706
- Merciful heaven.
- You don't believe I'll do it.

33:29.600 --> 33:31.864
Do you really want to take that chance?

33:37.200 --> 33:39.623
You've been ill, Mon/venna...

33:40.880 --> 33:43.383
...and I have no wish to see you relapse.

33:44.240 --> 33:46.219
I will leave you...

33:46.920 --> 33:49.900
...to think over your duty to me.

33:52.720 --> 33:55.382
I will pray to our Lord
to grant you forgiveness.

33:55.560 --> 33:57.539
(Baby cries)

34:11.600 --> 34:14.467
I didn't mean it.
Of course I didn't mean it.

34:15.640 --> 34:18.302
- But Drake be no harm to anyone.
- It beggars belief.

34:18.480 --> 34:20.345
Had he been found an hour later...

34:20.520 --> 34:22.499
Of course, Demelza asked me
not to tell you.

34:22.680 --> 34:24.500
She's afraid of what I might do to George.

34:24.680 --> 34:27.057
- As well she may be.
- Will you go to Trenwith?

34:27.240 --> 34:28.980
This instant.

34:30.280 --> 34:32.259
(Shooting practice continues)

34:37.600 --> 34:40.160
What is it?

34:40.320 --> 34:42.584
- Is it Drake?
- Agatha's grave.

34:45.000 --> 34:48.345
- Need we discuss that now?
- Things you need to attend to?

34:48.520 --> 34:50.306
What things?

34:50.480 --> 34:52.584
None that need concern you.

34:52.760 --> 34:54.387
That's convenient, Ross.

34:54.560 --> 34:57.620
No concern of mine
who you meet, who you talk to,

34:57.800 --> 34:59.461
who you kiss.

35:03.200 --> 35:05.020
It is not what you imagine.

35:05.200 --> 35:09.466
Ross, I am weary of it.
Secret kisses, secret smiles.

35:10.280 --> 35:12.987
How many other secrets
must there be between us?

35:16.240 --> 35:19.619
Keep them, Ross. Keep them all.

35:21.800 --> 35:23.779
And I will keep mine.

35:27.400 --> 35:29.379
Demelza.

35:33.880 --> 35:35.984
Urgent word from Truro, Captain.

35:43.320 --> 35:45.185
What is it? The French?

35:45.360 --> 35:48.227
The peace and safety of our country
is threatened.

35:48.400 --> 35:52.063
We're ordered to the northern road.
We must mobilise at once!

36:25.400 --> 36:26.981
Well...

36:28.200 --> 36:30.259
Can I make it any plainer?

36:30.440 --> 36:33.147
I abandoned my squadron
in the middle of a war...

36:34.120 --> 36:36.099
...to throw myself at your feet.

36:38.080 --> 36:41.060
Is there a more extravagant way
I could declare my love?

36:42.320 --> 36:44.697
A longer poem would have sufficed.

36:45.760 --> 36:47.546
Not for me.

36:53.600 --> 36:55.909
Shall we walk to Hendrawna Sands?

37:15.960 --> 37:18.064
May I take your hand?

37:18.240 --> 37:20.344
What if someone should see?

37:21.080 --> 37:23.457
I will tell them
that I need you to guide me.

37:25.960 --> 37:27.587
And very soon it will be true.

37:29.880 --> 37:31.825
I've been discharged from the Navy.

37:32.760 --> 37:34.546
For what?

37:34.720 --> 37:37.462
In six months' time,
I'll be completely blind.

38:20.080 --> 38:22.537
HUGH: I do not presume
to compare myself to Ross.

38:24.200 --> 38:28.148
He ’5 a great man.
My saviour and friend

38:36.640 --> 38:38.619
But you are...

38:38.800 --> 38:40.665
His wife.

38:40.840 --> 38:44.059
- And mother of his children.
- And I've no wish to threaten that.

38:45.360 --> 38:47.578
I would not allow it.

38:49.000 --> 38:50.706
Your head might not.

38:52.600 --> 38:54.659
But would your heart?

38:57.560 --> 38:59.778
HUGH:
It is to the heart
to which I now appeal

38:59.960 --> 39:02.064
and that part which, dare I say it

39:02.240 --> 39:04.299
has been neglected.

39:05.720 --> 39:07.699
Can you allow me this?

39:10.160 --> 39:12.344
Shall we grant ourselves to each other...

39:13.800 --> 39:16.303
...so that I may go into the darkness...

39:16.480 --> 39:20.223
knowing that I...
I once tasted heaven?

40:21.360 --> 40:23.339
(Cart rattling)

40:25.760 --> 40:28.467
(Shouting and rowdy chatter)

41:02.040 --> 41:05.100
THOLLY: We're here for the grain.
Stand aside.

41:05.960 --> 41:08.064
Take them home, Tholly.

41:10.440 --> 41:13.182
Your father would turn in his grave,

41:14.000 --> 41:18.778
his own son changing sides,
pandering to the pomp and privileged.

41:19.520 --> 41:22.500
When the French arrive,
you may wish to be elsewhere.

41:24.360 --> 41:27.909
THOLLY: There be no French.
Only threat to us here is thee.

41:34.720 --> 41:37.939
Will 'ee not take a stand with us,
brother?

41:38.840 --> 41:41.582
Will 'ee not show where thy loyalties lie?

41:41.760 --> 41:43.899
ROSS: You know where this leads, Tholly.

41:44.080 --> 41:47.584
Bloodshed. Riot.
We've both seen it.

41:47.760 --> 41:50.945
So go now and no harm will come to you!

41:51.120 --> 41:53.304
Folks is starving.

41:53.480 --> 41:55.664
You know who this grain store belong to?

41:56.920 --> 42:01.107
The man who battered thine own kin -
George Warleggan.

42:03.000 --> 42:06.026
Warleggan do think he's above the law!

42:06.200 --> 42:07.781
MOB: Aye!

42:08.600 --> 42:11.467
It's not thy duty to hold him to account?

42:11.640 --> 42:14.666
My duty is to king and country

42:14.840 --> 42:17.786
and I will do whatever it takes
to keep the peace.

42:22.840 --> 42:25.149
You have
until the count of ten to disperse.

42:26.760 --> 42:28.705
Or what, young captain?

42:31.120 --> 42:33.702
Or...what?

42:41.600 --> 42:43.659
Is this what they brought 'ee to?

42:44.560 --> 42:47.745
'Ee is so enthralled
with the establishment...

42:48.560 --> 42:52.189
...you'd subdue by force
your old comrades and friends?

42:52.360 --> 42:55.181
ROSS: You leave me no choice.

43:02.400 --> 43:04.960
One, two...

43:07.160 --> 43:09.617
...three, four...

43:11.560 --> 43:14.267
...five, six...

43:15.480 --> 43:17.903
...seven, eight...

43:18.840 --> 43:20.865
...nine...

43:28.800 --> 43:30.620
...ten.

43:32.400 --> 43:35.540
SIR FRANCIS: Terror, bloodshed
That is not democracy, that is vengeance.

43:35.720 --> 43:37.665
R055: I do not endorse bloodshed

43:37.840 --> 43:39.546
Demelza, I have never been that man.

43:39.720 --> 43:42.939
