44:01.720 --> 44:04.029
You're right, my friend.

44:06.000 --> 44:08.457
Of course, I've changed sides.

44:09.800 --> 44:11.745
I'm not here to defend my country,

44:12.840 --> 44:16.025
but to protect the property
of my good friend, George,

44:16.200 --> 44:19.897
who would like nothing better than
for me to pick up arms against you.

44:21.680 --> 44:24.547
But the time has come
to take a stand against him.

44:26.320 --> 44:28.299
But not just here...

44:30.600 --> 44:32.739
...but in the corridors of Westminster.

44:33.680 --> 44:35.386
That much is clear now.

44:36.360 --> 44:40.581
So the next time I'm asked
to stand for public office...

44:43.960 --> 44:46.383
...can you imagine what my answer will be?

44:52.000 --> 44:53.979
THOLLY: Good lad.

45:29.200 --> 45:31.760
Elizabeth. I must...

45:34.400 --> 45:37.984
Are you saying that my doubts,
my suspicions,

45:38.160 --> 45:40.617
are completely unfounded?

45:45.920 --> 45:48.104
Name them and I will tell you.

45:52.840 --> 45:56.139
L...believe...

45:59.400 --> 46:01.960
I believe that you...

46:02.120 --> 46:04.224
still love Ross.

46:05.720 --> 46:09.349
No, George. That is not all you believe.

46:09.520 --> 46:12.660
- Is it not enough?
- More than enough.

46:12.840 --> 46:16.469
No doubt it's why you set your creatures
to follow me day and night,

46:17.080 --> 46:19.503
but that is not all, is it?

46:24.160 --> 46:26.264
Is it?

46:27.840 --> 46:30.741
Ah, I... Iwill...dismiss Tom Harry.

46:30.920 --> 46:33.138
I will repair the boy's smithy
at my own expense.

46:33.320 --> 46:37.381
Tell me why you treat your son
as if he were not your son.

46:40.720 --> 46:42.859
Is he my son?

46:45.920 --> 46:48.559
Who else's could he be?

46:56.080 --> 47:00.107
Now you see how jealousy is eating you up?

47:00.280 --> 47:01.747
I cannot abide it.

47:02.560 --> 47:04.619
I will not abide it.

47:04.800 --> 47:06.825
No, no, Elizabeth, please. I...

47:11.640 --> 47:16.100
I swear that I have never given myself
to another man,

47:16.280 --> 47:18.703
except my first husband, Francis, and you.

47:24.240 --> 47:27.869
But, of course,
even that will not satisfy you.

47:28.640 --> 47:31.905
So I will leave Trenwith today,
taking Geoffrey Charles and Valentine.

47:32.080 --> 47:34.822
No, no, Elizabeth, wait, I beg you.

47:35.000 --> 47:36.581
Perhaps I was...

47:36.760 --> 47:40.389
Perhaps... Perhaps I was too hasty.

47:40.560 --> 47:44.985
As you say, there have been suspicions -
unfounded, clearly unjust.

47:45.160 --> 47:48.140
I've been misguided

47:48.320 --> 47:53.144
and yet...you must see that this is
only a reflection of my regard,

47:53.320 --> 47:55.777
of my love, of my very great love.

47:55.960 --> 47:57.939
Is love cruel?

47:58.800 --> 48:01.018
Is love unkind?

48:01.200 --> 48:05.546
Is your bitter bile
coldness towards me and your son...

48:05.720 --> 48:07.779
It will cease, from this moment.

48:07.960 --> 48:09.939
So will my jealousy, so my suspicions.

48:10.120 --> 48:11.860
Swear it.

48:13.920 --> 48:16.184
I have sworn, so must you.

48:19.880 --> 48:25.420
You will never again speak
or even harbour such vile suspicions

48:25.600 --> 48:27.306
about your wife and child.

48:27.480 --> 48:29.539
I will not. I swear it.

48:30.400 --> 48:34.507
I will never...never again.

48:42.200 --> 48:44.179
Forgive me.

48:46.640 --> 48:48.619
Forgive me.

48:53.600 --> 48:55.579
I forgive you.

48:56.720 --> 48:58.779
Is Westminster ready for Ross Poldark?

48:58.960 --> 49:00.905
Ready or not, change is long overdue.

49:01.080 --> 49:03.184
When next it's offered,
I believe he'll accept.

49:03.360 --> 49:05.464
I have some changes of my own
I'd like to propose.

49:05.640 --> 49:09.747
Do they involve less patients,
less training with the volunteers?

49:09.920 --> 49:14.141
And, in their place, more kisses,
more bonbons and more lying abed.

49:14.320 --> 49:17.904
- Bonbons are bad for the health.
- But kisses are the cure for everything.

49:21.680 --> 49:23.261
(Growls softly)

49:23.440 --> 49:25.419
(Birdsong)

49:28.600 --> 49:30.579
(Door opens and closes)

49:32.480 --> 49:34.141
(Footsteps)

49:36.000 --> 49:38.662
- Where's Demelza?
- Out.

49:40.360 --> 49:42.146
Where?

49:43.200 --> 49:44.986
She didn't say.

49:47.640 --> 49:49.221
Alone?

49:51.520 --> 49:53.545
Had a visitor.

50:04.120 --> 50:05.587
Is she coming back?

50:06.920 --> 50:08.342
Expect so.

50:10.200 --> 50:11.667
She didn't say.

50:14.880 --> 50:16.859
(Birdsong)

50:23.080 --> 50:24.945
Thought I would die today.

50:29.240 --> 50:30.582
I, too.

50:31.640 --> 50:35.861
But when I did not, I began to think

50:36.040 --> 50:39.100
life has some purpose
that I knowed not till now.

50:40.840 --> 50:42.467
Why think you so?

50:44.080 --> 50:49.985
For this day, I found green shoots
coming up, out of season.

50:53.120 --> 50:54.781
And what shoots they be?

50:57.400 --> 50:59.379
Winter primroses.

51:03.600 --> 51:05.067
(He laughs)

52:05.320 --> 52:07.345
Well, Ross...

52:07.520 --> 52:11.502
My compliments to the volunteers.
I believe they were put to good use today.

52:14.680 --> 52:17.660
Oh, did you think you were being summoned
to fight the Frenchies?

52:17.840 --> 52:21.264
No, it seems Tom Harry
got the better of you.

52:21.440 --> 52:24.580
A little nudge and your muskets
protect my grain store.

52:24.760 --> 52:31.700
But you humble foot soldiers must go
where your betters decree, I believe.

52:35.000 --> 52:37.423
And what else do you believe, George?

52:42.120 --> 52:44.759
I believe I have _
every reason for optimism.

52:46.200 --> 52:50.387
I believe I have a devoted wife,
a thriving son, a fine estate

52:50.560 --> 52:53.620
and a parliamentary career
which has barely begun.

52:53.800 --> 52:55.939
What is it you believe, Ross?

53:00.120 --> 53:02.782
That belief is a beautiful thing.

53:21.200 --> 53:22.747
(Birdsong outside)

53:26.920 --> 53:28.820
(Knocking)

54:01.240 --> 54:03.219
Wherever you are...

54:05.200 --> 54:07.543
...know that I love you.

54:58.480 --> 55:00.459
(Snoring)

55:34.400 --> 55:36.379
(Door opens)

55:47.760 --> 55:49.500
(Door closes)

55:55.480 --> 55:57.459
I thought you might not return.

56:00.000 --> 56:01.979
I thought so, too.

56:05.720 --> 56:07.699
Yet here I am.

56:50.400 --> 56:52.379
Demelza.

56:54.480 --> 56:56.459
- May I ask?
- No, Ross.

56:57.960 --> 56:59.746
Ask me nothing.
